data.title: Ukraine
data.text:
I❤️UKRAINE!

Especially Kropyvnytskyi!

Kropyvnytskyi is a city located in the valley and on the banks of the Inhul River in the central part of Ukraine, about 300 km southeast of Kyiv. It is the administrative center of Kirovohrad Oblast, an important industrial and cultural center of the country. The population of Kropyvnytskyi is about 222,700 (2021), the area - 103 sq. km.

Kropyvnytskyi is named after the Ukrainian writer and playwright Marko Kropyvnytskyi (1840-1910), who created the first Ukrainian professional theater while living in this city. The City Day of Kropyvnytskyi is celebrated on the 3rd Saturday of September.
